TopicTitle: Game crashes when ragdoll kerbals touch the ground

Articles.Content:
Had that happen this morning. This is what my ship landed on Minimus now looks like, along with my all-star pilot. I'm pretty pissed off, about it.

[http://imageshack.com/a/img673/810/22th7C.jpg](http://imageshack.com/a/img673/810/22th7C.jpg)

It's ridiculous. I've started cheating and replacing my quicksaves with the persistence file (my career doesn't allow quickloads) because half the time i'm expecting my ship to randomly explode or for some other glitch to break the save. I don't really like to rant but i'm pretty salty about this. I'm disappointed that this is a fully released game now and yet it still has, IMHO, some major bugs that still need to be addressed.

I was having the same problem and believe to have found the reason for the bug... it was only happening to me when I pushed 'r' immediately after letting go of the ladder. I have done it several times by not pushing anything and letting the kerbal ragdoll to the ground and everything was fine. Then when I pressed 'r' right after pushing 'space' to let go of ladder, it crashed again. I couldn't find a solution anywhere but from my limited testing it seems to work. Hopefully this works.
